  "text": "I found a phone ringing in the middle of an empty parking lot. No cars. No people. Just the phone, face down, buzzing against the concrete. I picked it up. The screen said: **Mom**. I almost didn’t answer. But something felt wrong. So I swiped. Before I could speak, a woman whispered, “Don’t turn around.” My stomach dropped. I froze. Then I heard it. Footsteps behind me. Slow. One step. Then another. The woman on the phone started crying. 'Please,' she said. 'He already has my son.' I turned anyway. And standing under the only broken streetlight… was a little boy. Holding my exact same phone. And it was ringing too.",
